-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-BNP Paribas, British Land Co, Swisscom, Volvo
-- 
-- Mon Apr 28, 2014 03:57AM EDT
-- None



April 28 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including British Land Co, Gemalto, Swisscom and Volvo, on Monday.

HIGHLIGHTS * British Land Company <BLND.L>: JP Morgan raises to overweight from neutral rating * Gemalto <GTO.AS>: S&P Capital IQ cuts to hold from buy rating * Swisscom <SCMN.VX>: Berenberg cuts to sell from hold rating Following is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Monday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.  * Air Liquide SA <AIRP.PA>: JP Morgan raises target to 117 euros from 115 euros; overweight * Arseus NV <RCUS.BR>: Jefferies raises target price to 45 euros from 34 euros; rating buy * BNP Paribas SA <BNPP.PA>: Citigroup cuts target price to 68 euros from 71 euros; buy * British Land Company <BLND.L>: JP Morgan raises to overweight from neutral * British Land Company <BLND.L>: JP Morgan raises target price to 740p from 680p  * Gemalto <GTO.AS>: S&P Capital IQ cuts to hold from buy * QSC AG <QSCG.DE>: JP Morgan cuts target price to 4.40 euros from 4.90 euros; overweight * Shire PLC <SHP.L>: Berenberg raises target price to 3400p from 2900p; rating hold  * Standard Chartered <STAN.L>: Jefferies cuts target price to 1000p from 1100p; underperform * Swisscom <SCMN.VX>: Berenberg cuts to sell from hold; raises target to Sfr 450 from 408  * Telecity Group <TCY.L>: JP Morgan cuts target price to 900p from 1100p; rating overweight